  <guide>
    <section section_id="overview" title="Overview">
      <p>Vibrant Voyage is a late-game gem spend event with strong returns once you have three etched rune slots and partial chaotic gear.</p>
      <p>If you are not there yet, stop at the 125-ticket milestone for consistent value.</p>
    </section>
    <section section_id="milestones" title="Gem Spending Milestones">
      <p>Everyone should target the 125-ticket milestone. The keys from this milestone plus marks from tickets typically exceed the gem cost.</p>
      <p>On average you will buy around 30 tickets (about 8,400 gems) and gain roughly 4,500 to 5,500 wayfarer marks.</p>
      <p>If you plan to go past 125, choose a later milestone (200 or 300 are common stops). The 300 milestone yields around 11,000 to 14,000 marks.</p>
      <p>All relevant milestones shown below, after 1000 you gain the same reward for every 500 tickets spent.</p>
      <image_row>
        <image src="catalog/shared/vibrant_voyage_event/media/misc/vv_milestones_1.png" alt="Milestones 75–200 tickets" />
        <image src="catalog/shared/vibrant_voyage_event/media/misc/vv_milestones_2.png" alt="Milestones 300–1000 tickets" />
      </image_row>
    </section>
    <section section_id="shop_priorities" title="What To Buy">
      <p>If you still need chaotic gear, prioritize keys and stop at 125.</p>
      <p>Discount S-tier gear can be worth it if you do not need fodder. Discount gear is about 32 keys, non-discount gear is about 65 keys, and weapons are 100+ keys.</p>
      <p>When you are ready to spend more, tidal star cores or mythic artifacts are ideal.</p>
      <p>Best first mythic artifact: Voidblade. After that, focus on artifacts that buff your main damage type.</p>
      <p>Character skins: follow the Character and Skin Choice Guide. Weapon skins are mostly cosmetic.</p>
    </section>
  </guide>
  <faq>
    <item faq_id="why_125" question="Why is the 125-ticket milestone recommended?">
      <answer>
        <p>The keys plus marks at 125 typically return more value than the gem cost, even at average luck.</p>
      </answer>
    </item>
    <item faq_id="when_go_beyond" question="When should I go past 125 tickets?">
      <answer>
        <p>Only after you have three etched rune slots and partial chaotic gear. Otherwise the 125 stop is the best value.</p>
      </answer>
    </item>
    <item faq_id="best_shop_buys" question="What are the best shop purchases?">
      <answer>
        <p>Keys if you still need chaotic gear. Later, tidal star cores or mythic artifacts. Voidblade is the best first mythic artifact.</p>
      </answer>
    </item>
    <item faq_id="weapon_skins" question="Are weapon skins worth it?">
      <answer>
        <p>They are mostly cosmetic. Buy them for looks, not for power.</p>
      </answer>
    </item>
    <item faq_id="marks_per_ticket" question="How many wayfarer marks per ticket?">
      <answer>
        <p>About 40 to 43 marks per ticket on average.</p>
      </answer>
    </item>
    <item faq_id="balloon_rate" question="How often do balloon rides happen?">
      <answer>
        <p>Roughly 1 ride per 100 tickets on average, plus the guaranteed ride.</p>
      </answer>
    </item>
    <item faq_id="f2p_tickets" question="How many tickets can free-to-play players get?">
      <answer>
        <p>After the 7 ad tickets, about 95 total tickets without buying any directly.</p>
      </answer>
    </item>
  </faq>
